  "text": "␥-Catenin ϩ/Ϫ mice, [CITATION_1] backcrossed more than 10 times to B6 (CD45.2 ϩ ), were intercrossed. Embryos were obtained at day 12.5 of gestation and were genotyped by PCR as described. 14 Recipient B6 CD45.1 ϩ mice were lethally irradiated (9.6 Gy [960 rad], 137-Cs source) before intravenous injection of 5 ϫ 10 6 fetal liver cells. Chimeras were analyzed 3 to 5 months after reconstitution.",
